HEADWORD: Serolin
<hw>Ser"o*lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Ser</ets>um +
L. <ets>ole</ets>um oil.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>A peculiar fatty substance found in the blood, probably a mixture
of fats, cholesterin, etc.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A body found in fecal
matter and thought to be formed in the intestines from the cholesterin
of the bile; -- called also <altname>stercorin</altname>, and
<altname>stercolin</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

